:: Forest Wraith Gwylan 9
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<if $control gte $controlmax>>
	<span class="gold">You stop.</span> The pale figure doesn't. It flies out of your body as it lunges for Gwylan.
	<br><br>

	<<if $wraith.state is "haunt">>
		<<He>> ducks, narrowly avoiding being raked by its blackened arm
	<<else>>
		<<He>> ducks, narrowly avoiding being grabbed
	<</if>>
	as it soars right past <<him>>. <<He>> rushes to your side, helping you stand as the numbness fades from your body. <<He>> stands protectively between you and it.
	<br><br>

	"This is my home. You have no power here. Begone." The entire shop seems to shudder in response. <span class="purple">Dozens of wooden mannequins stand behind the pale figure, each one making a grab for it.</span>
	<br><br>

	It waves its hand, and wooden limbs are scattered everywhere as a single pale tendril whips across them.
	<<if $wraith.state is "haunt">>
		It sneers. "<span class="wraith">Cruel gull. <<pShe>> is mine. If not on this night, then the next. I will wait forever if need be.</span>"
	<<else>>
		It laughs. "<span class="wraith">Clever gull. <<pShe>> is mine. I know you understand. To be alone forever-</span>"
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	"You aren't ready for forever," Gwylan says back. "You aren't even ready for right now." <<He>> raises a hand and snaps <<his>> fingers.
	The mannequins stand again, and despite many missing arms, they all approach. Most are knocked away and broken further, but a few find their mark, restraining its limbs. It simply sprouts more, which grab and tear the mannequins apart.
	<br><br>

	It turns back with a smug grin, just in time for a ?gwylanItem to bounce off of its head with a loud thud. Its head is knocked to a tilt. It looks stunned for a moment, as if surprised it was actually hit by that.
	It was just a distraction, though. Gwylan runs towards it, a golden bracelet in hand. <<He>> clasps it around the figure's arm, and yells a command.
	<br><br>

	<b>"<span class="witch">Go home!</span>"</b>
	<br><br>

	A matching golden shackle appears around the bracelet. The nearest window flies open on its own as Gwylan darts back to your side. <span class="purple">A screeching wind rips through the air, towards the window.</span> The figure is yanked towards it.
	Its many hands grip the window frame for purchase, but each one becomes clasped in another golden shackle. It gives you both one last piercing look, before <span class="green">it's expelled from the shop</span>.
<<else>>
	Gwylan ducks, narrowly avoiding your lunge. You land behind <<him>> and turn.
	<br><br>

	"This is my home. You have no power here. Begone." The entire shop seems to shudder in response. <span class="purple">Dozens of wooden hands wrap around your arms and legs. You're surrounded by mannequins.</span>
	<br><br>

	Your body struggles against them.
	<<if $wraith.state is "haunt">>
		It sneers. "<span class="wraith">Cruel gull. <<pShe>> is mine. Join us. We can share this bliss forever.</span>"
	<<else>>
		It laughs. "<span class="wraith">Clever gull. <<pShe>> is mine. Join us. We can share this bliss forever.</span>"
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	"You aren't ready for forever," Gwylan says back. "You aren't even ready for right now."
	<<if $hypnosis_traits.devotion gte 4>>
		<<He>> slowly, but confidently, walks up to you and places a hand on your head. You don't feel it. "Besides, you're wrong. <<pShes>> mine." <<He>> giggles, before whispering in your ear.
		<br><br>

		<b>"<span class="witch">Sit.</span>"</b>
		<br><br>

		<<hypnosisText "<span class='blue'>Your body sits obediently.</span>">> The mannequins all release you.
		<br><br>

		The Wraith pushes against you, trying to force you to move. <span class="green">It can't.</span> You continue to sit in place.
		"<<pcPetname "Gwylan" "good">>." <<He>> pets your head. You can feel it. The numbness is fading. <<trauma -1>><<ltrauma>><<gcontrol>>
		<br><br>

		<<He>> turns your head to face the nearest window, and whispers another command.
	<<else>>
		<<He>> grabs a ?gwylanItem from a nearby shelf, tosses it up and down in <<his>> hand for a moment, and <span class="red">whips it at you</span>.
		<br><br>

		It bounces off of your head with a loud thud, but you don't feel any pain. The intruder feels rattled, though. Just enough for you to exert your will for a precious moment. <<gcontrol>>
		<br><br>

		Gwylan runs up to you, and turns your head to face the nearest window. <<He>> whispers a command into your ear.
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<b>"<span class="witch">Go home.</span>"</b>
	<br><br>

	The window flies open on its own. Your vision focuses on something, far into the forest. The trees seem to part for you. It's the lake.
	<span class="purple">A screeching wind rips through the air, towards it.</span> The figure is pulled out of your body.
	Its many hands grip the window frame for purchase, but each one becomes clasped in a golden shackle. It gives you both one last piercing look, before <span class="green">it's expelled from the shop</span>.
<</if>>
<br><br>

The window slams shut. Gwylan holds you tightly.
<br><br>

